amples.  I would have to write a book to go through all of them.  Bottom line is, believe what you want, that is your right.  However, no one should EVER make any beliefs of this matter without doing research yourself.  If you believe what you believe just because that is how you were raised and taught, shame on you.  Go out and learn on your own, then make your decision, whether it is about the existence of God, or or whether you prefer Chevy over Ford.  The only time I will ever attack anyone for their beliefs is if they just blindly believe them with no reason except that is what they know.  I have 100 times the respect for the devout atheist that believes what he believes because he took the time to study and make up his own mind what he believes than the band-wagon christian that shares my beliefs just because he or she was raised that way.   <br>
