This covers a majority of the beliefs out there, and begins with a truth - since we are all sure to die. <br>
<br>
For the most part, I don't believe in a god, because he is too mysterious. For that same reason, I don't believe in a Big Bang. So how did I come to be? I don't know, and don't have the resources to find out. Therefore, I choose not to dwell on that which is ambiguous enough to complicate my short life and in the end give me no truth, only beliefs - but what good are beliefs when you're dead?<br>
<br>
Supposing that I:<br>
<br>
- Return to that plane of truth, somewhere that beliefs would be useless, since the truth is available and absolute.<br>
<br>
- Return as another life; but if I believe this, then I know I can't remember my past lives, and the beliefs of this life will therefore no longer serve me.<br>
<br>
- Stand before a god? Does he care about my beliefs, or only my actions? Do I have to die for my god, or just go to church in order to be saved? How often do I have to go to church? Must I not commit 'sins', or can I simply ask for this god's forgiveness? The chance that my beliefs in life will lead me into favor with such an ambiguous god seem stageringly small.<br>
<br>
- And if death is the end, in the same way that billions, trillions, or perhaps an infinite amount of time passed instantly for me before I was concious - the rest of eternity will elapse in the same manner and my beliefs will have been absolutely nothing in the sceme of everything.<br>
<br>
<br>
So -- I live my life not worrying about things which are so ambiguous. I accept that either Something or Nothing will happen when I die, and I choose to accept that I cannot change what happens. If people decide they must devote themselves to accumulating beliefs - I only ask they stay out of my way, because my life is short and I while I'm living it, I don't need your annoyances.<br>
<br>
I suppose if you like labels you can put me in your little folder under skeptic. If what you like to do is gather beliefs about others, anyway.<br>
<br>
